<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Vitality boosts the amount of experience you get in the first few encounters of a given session.  Once Vitality is used up, you level at a normal rate.  Vitality is already in game and has been since release.  They are just adding a window so you can see how much adventurer and artisan Vitality you have.
<br />

<br />
Vitality refreshes very slowly (one RL week to go from empty to full).
<br />

<br />
It is similar to WoW's rest system.  An optimistic way to view it is that it helps casual players keep pace with their hardcore friends by giving them more experience per encounter.  A pessimistic way to view it is that it punishes people who like to grind experience in long sessions by rewarding them with less experience per encounter in the latter part of their sessions.
<br />

<br />
dgarbini is right; they are planning to change Vitality.  The current system has different bonuses depending on how much Vitality you have used.  The proposed system will have a fixed bonus no matter how much Vitality you have.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
